    "body": "What's the status of this? I've been playing around with Viper and have noticed that `pyethereum` is the only client with support for a `decimal` ABI (since commit https://github.com/ethereum/pyethereum/commit/237df71d1eafeafaafd6bca16d0ba066f3d1fff3).\r\n\r\nElsewhere, there is discussion of using the `fixed` types to implement Viper's `decimal` (here: https://github.com/ethereum/vyper/issues/566).\r\n\r\nI would really like to be able to (easily) use `decimal` values in Populus, but I don't want to hack the \"wrong\" approach into `web3.py` (upon which Populus depends).",
